bash 

-- > Basic Scan 
nmap <target>
Scans the top 1000 most common ports.
Use when: You want a general overview of a target.

--> Fast Scan
nmap -F <target>
Scans only the top 100 ports.
Use when: You need quick results and don't need a full scan.

--> Scan Specific Ports
nmap -p 22,80,443 <target>
Scans only the ports you specify.
Use when: You know exactly which services you want to check.

--> Scan a Port Range
nmap -p 1-100 <target>
Scans all ports in the given range.
Use when: You want to check a block of ports.

--> Scan All Ports
nmap -p- <target>
Scans all 65535 ports.
Use when: Thorough audit, finding hidden services on unusual ports.

--> Scan Top N Ports
nmap --top-ports 10 <target>
Scans the N most commonly used ports.
Use when: Quick targeted check without scanning everything.


